		<body xml:lang="en">
			<div>

	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_001282_0001"/><!--pb/@n='1r'-->
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName>Birkenhead</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">8<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> March 1858</p>
<lb/><p>Dear <persName>Captain Washington</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I duly <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> all 
<lb/>your enclosures for 
<lb/><placeName>Sierra Leone</placeName> and the 
<lb/><placeName>Cape</placeName> on the 7<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> and 
<lb/>return the agreement 
<lb/>with the signature of 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001282_0002"/><!--pb/@n='1v'--> 
<lb/>the engineer annexed. 
<lb/>We are all ready for 
<lb/>embarcation and nothing 
<lb/>but the weather, which 
<lb/>was excessively bad 
<lb/>all yesterday, will 
<lb/>prevent our sailing 
<lb/>about noon.</p>
<lb/><p>I beg leave again 
<lb/>to express my grateful 
<lb/>sense of your very 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001282_0003"/><!--pb/@n='2r'--> 
<lb/>great and constant 
<lb/>kindness throughout the 
<lb/>preparation of this expedition<reg>.</reg>
<lb/>I tender you my 
<lb/>cordial thanks for all 
<lb/>the labour &amp; anxiety 
<lb/>you have so patiently 
<lb/>undergone in our 
<lb/>behalf and I hope 
<lb/>your good wishes 
<lb/>may be realized 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001282_0004"/><!--pb/@n='2v'--> 
<lb/>by every one of us 
<lb/>effectually doing our 
<lb/>duty<reg>.</reg></p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am yours</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">very cordially</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p>9 A.M. weather very stormy 
<lb/>with snow. If the pilots 
<lb/>say we may venture out 
<lb/>we shall do so about 
<lb/>12. I sign <persName>M<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Laird's</persName>
<lb/>account for the launch as 
<lb/>an aid though it may not be 
<lb/>quite essential<reg>.</reg> D. L.</p>
			
</div>
